ation. Of Llull's works, it offers Book of the Gentile and the Three Wise Men, his seminal Christian apology; the Ars brevis, a summary of his philosophical system; The Book of the Lover and the Beloved, a celebration of mystical love in the courtly tradition; and his wittily scathing Book of the Beasts.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aApologeticsxEarly works to 1800. 0aMysticismxEarly works to 1800. 0aPhilosophyxEarly works to 1800. 0aTheologyxEarly works to 1800. 7aBODY, MIND & SPIRIT / Mysticism.2bisacsh  aAbraham.  aAdam.  aAngevin dynasty.  aBabylonians.  aBarcelona.  aBonllavi, Joan.  aBruno, Giordano.  aCandellero, Massimo.  aCastro, Américo.  aColomer, Eusebi.  aCusa, Nicholas of.  aDominican Order.  aFigure A (First Figure).  aFigure X.  aFigure, Demonstrative.  aForms, Hundred.  aIbn Khaldun.  aIncarnation.  aJacobites.  aJerusalem.  aJews.  aJulian of Norwich.  aKnowles, David.  aKoran.  aLyon.  aMajorca.  aMediterranean, western.  aMunkar.  aNeoplatonism.  aOxford.  aPerpignan.  aaccidie.  aal-Ghazzali.  aalchemy.  aalteration.  acategories (predicaments).  acorrelatives.  adefinitions, Lullian.  adignities.  aelements, four.  aeternity of the world.  aexpulsion.  afullness.  ageneration and corruption (decay).  aguiding.  aheart.  ahonor.  alaw.  amedicine.  amixture.  anecessity.  aoccasion.  aproportion.1 aBonner, Anthony, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press eBook-Package Archive 1927-1999z978311044249608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press eBook-Package Gap Yearsz978311078423740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780691221991?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://w